<p>Using <code>Data.Typeable</code>, I can reify the type of a value -</p>  <pre><code>typeOf :: Typeable a =&gt; a -&gt; TypeRep </code></pre>  <p>However, given a <code>TypeRep</code>, there seems to be no way to "set" a value to that type.</p>  <p>For example -</p>  <pre><code>maybeIntType :: TypeRep maybeIntType = typeOf (Just 100 :: Maybe Int) </code></pre>  <p>But how do I use <code>maybeIntType</code> to create a <code>(Nothing :: Maybe Int)</code>?</p>